<Base title="About" description="From hunting bugs to building intelligent systems — the story behind ihabnk.">

  <article class="article-col">

    <!-- Kicker -->
    <div class="article-kicker">whoami · about the site</div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <h1 class="article-headline">From hunting bugs to building intelligent systems.</h1>

    <!-- Dek -->
    <p class="article-dek">A QA engineer's pivot into AI product building — and why quality is the most underrated skill in the age of autonomous agents.</p>

    <!-- Meta strip -->
    <div class="article-meta">
      <span class="author">Ihab NK</span>
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span>Quality Engineer → AI Builder</span>
      <span class="dot"></span>
      <span>Riyadh, KSA</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Body -->
    <div class="article-body prose max-w-none">
      <p>I started my career in quality engineering, where I learned that understanding how systems fail is the most powerful tool a software engineer can have. I spent years building test frameworks, managing product quality, and leading Scrum teams shipping software people could rely on.</p>

      <p>Then AI changed the rules of the game. Instead of resisting the shift, I saw an opportunity: my background in quality made me uniquely qualified to build the next generation of tools. The people who understand how systems break are the same people who should build the systems we trust.</p>

      <div class="pullquote">
        "Quality isn't a phase that comes after building. It's the mindset that makes building possible."
      </div>

      <h2>Why this site?</h2>
      <p>I write here for people who want to understand the shift happening in software — not just use new tools, but think in new ways:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>QA engineers who want to understand how AI is reshaping their role.</li>
        <li>Scrum Masters and Product Managers leading teams adopting new tooling.</li>
        <li>Anyone who wants to understand technology — not just use it.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Where to find me</h2>
      <p>I publish tools and frameworks on <a href="https://github.com/ihabnk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>, and share reflections on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/ihabnk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>. If something I write helps you, a coffee always makes my week.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="glow-sep" style="margin:40px 0 32px"></div>

